    "Terence E. Fretheim, Thomas B. Slater": "; as Jeremiah\nhad requested in 18:21!). God will strike them with a \u201cpestilence\u201d\n[v_Exo_9_15] such as Egypt experienced (see 16:4; see Exod 9:15; about which\n[v_Lev_26_25] Israel was warned, see Lev 26:25; Deut 28:21). Note also that both\nhuman beings and animals are adversely affected by this invasion\n(\nv. 6; see 7:20; 12:1-11). The piling up of words for anger in\nv. 6 (see 24:8-10). They will be given into the hands of others, also\nnamed in three ways: King Nebuchadrezzar, their enemies, and\nthose who have sought to kill them. It is an\nespecially sharp blow that the Davidic king,\nabout whom God has made such key promises\n[v_2Sa_7_14] [v_2Sa_7_15] [v_2Sa_7_16] (see 2 Sam 7:14-16), will be taken into exile\n(texts such as\nwith this reality). Jeremiah will assure exilic\nreaders in no uncertain terms that God will not\nrenege on these promises (e.g., 23:1-6; 30:9;\n33:14-26).\nThe last sentence of"
